<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,1164,1947]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1416,1442]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Description.</emphasis>
Habit elongate or massive. The size of the specimen with an elongate habit (CNPGG-2264, 
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 45" captionStartId="50.[151,250,1742,1766]" captionTargetBox="[200,1387,181,1719]" captionTargetId="figure-27@50.[200,1387,181,1719]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="FIGURE 45. In situ photographs of species analyzed in the present study: A. Neopetrosia proxima Duchassaing &amp; Michelotti, 1864 (CNPGG-2264); B. Neopetrosia proxima Duchassaing &amp; Michelotti, 1864 (CNPGG-2376); C. Neopetrosia subtriangularis (Duchassaing, 1850) (CNPGG-2435); D. Petrosia (Petrosia) weinbergi van Soest, 1980 (CNPGG-2434). E. Xestospongia muta (Schmidt, 1870) (CNPGG-2230); F. Siphonodictyon xamaycaense Pulitzer-Finali, 1986 (CNPGG-2441), arrows pointing to fistules; G. Siphonodictyon xamaycaense Pulitzer-Finali, 1986 (CNPGG-2432); H. Clathria (Clathria) foliacea Topsent, 1889 (CNPGG-2172), its stem is covered by algae; I. Clathria (Clathria) gomezae van Soest, 2017 (CNPGG-2231); J. Clathria (Thalysias) venosa (Alcolado, 1984) (CNPGG-2410); K. Clathria (Thalysias) virgultosa (Esper, 1806) (CNPGG-2357). Scale bars, A–K = 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5454470" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5454470/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 45A</figureCitation>
), ca. 20 × 6 × 
<quantity box="[368,428,1453,1479]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" unit="cm" value="2.0">2 cm</quantity>
. The larger massive specimen (CNPGG-2376, 
<figureCitation box="[959,1061,1452,1479]" captionStart="FIGURE 45" captionStartId="50.[151,250,1742,1766]" captionTargetBox="[200,1387,181,1719]" captionTargetId="figure-27@50.[200,1387,181,1719]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="FIGURE 45. In situ photographs of species analyzed in the present study: A. Neopetrosia proxima Duchassaing &amp; Michelotti, 1864 (CNPGG-2264); B. Neopetrosia proxima Duchassaing &amp; Michelotti, 1864 (CNPGG-2376); C. Neopetrosia subtriangularis (Duchassaing, 1850) (CNPGG-2435); D. Petrosia (Petrosia) weinbergi van Soest, 1980 (CNPGG-2434). E. Xestospongia muta (Schmidt, 1870) (CNPGG-2230); F. Siphonodictyon xamaycaense Pulitzer-Finali, 1986 (CNPGG-2441), arrows pointing to fistules; G. Siphonodictyon xamaycaense Pulitzer-Finali, 1986 (CNPGG-2432); H. Clathria (Clathria) foliacea Topsent, 1889 (CNPGG-2172), its stem is covered by algae; I. Clathria (Clathria) gomezae van Soest, 2017 (CNPGG-2231); J. Clathria (Thalysias) venosa (Alcolado, 1984) (CNPGG-2410); K. Clathria (Thalysias) virgultosa (Esper, 1806) (CNPGG-2357). Scale bars, A–K = 1 cm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5454470" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5454470/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 45B</figureCitation>
), ca. 20 ×10 × 
<quantity box="[1233,1293,1453,1479]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" unit="cm" value="2.0">2 cm</quantity>
. Surface microhispid and undulated. Oscules are slightly aligned (elongate specimen) or scattered (massive specimen). Color 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">in vivo</emphasis>
pale orange, pinkish-beige, or brownish-beige preserved in ethanol. The consistency is hard but friable.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,1164,1947]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,309,1560,1586]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Skeleton.</emphasis>
Ectosome is not easily detachable, and the tangential skeleton shows a rounded mesh; ca. 150–200 µm in diameter (
<figureCitation box="[341,447,1596,1623]" captionStart="FIGURE 33" captionStartId="40.[151,250,734,758]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,710]" captionTargetId="figure-27@40.[151,1435,181,710]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURE 33. Neopetrosia proxima Duchassaing &amp; Michelotti, 1864 (CNPGG-2264), skeleton and spicules: A. tangential section of the skeleton of the ectosomal region; B. transversal section of the skeleton; C. oxeas. Scale bars: A–B = 500 µm; C = 50 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5454446" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5454446/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 33A</figureCitation>
). Choanosome with a similar skeleton arrangement to the ectosomal skeleton. The choanosomal region with wide channels; up to 1500 µm width (
<figureCitation box="[826,929,1632,1659]" captionStart="FIGURE 33" captionStartId="40.[151,250,734,758]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,710]" captionTargetId="figure-27@40.[151,1435,181,710]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURE 33. Neopetrosia proxima Duchassaing &amp; Michelotti, 1864 (CNPGG-2264), skeleton and spicules: A. tangential section of the skeleton of the ectosomal region; B. transversal section of the skeleton; C. oxeas. Scale bars: A–B = 500 µm; C = 50 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5454446" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5454446/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 33B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,1164,1947]" box="[199,1289,1668,1695]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,304,1668,1694]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Spicules.</emphasis>
Megascleres: Oxeas, slightly curved (
<figureCitation box="[732,835,1668,1695]" captionStart="FIGURE 33" captionStartId="40.[151,250,734,758]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,710]" captionTargetId="figure-27@40.[151,1435,181,710]" captionTargetPageId="40" captionText="FIGURE 33. Neopetrosia proxima Duchassaing &amp; Michelotti, 1864 (CNPGG-2264), skeleton and spicules: A. tangential section of the skeleton of the ectosomal region; B. transversal section of the skeleton; C. oxeas. Scale bars: A–B = 500 µm; C = 50 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5454446" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5454446/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 33C</figureCitation>
); 132– 
<emphasis box="[912,954,1669,1695]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">147</emphasis>
(10)–165/7– 
<emphasis box="[1099,1134,1669,1695]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">9.2</emphasis>
(1.3)–12 µm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="39" pageNumber="40" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,1164,1947]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,1704,1730]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[359,445,1704,1730]" name="Mexico" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Mexico</collectingCountry>
(current records), 
<collectingCountry box="[650,686,1705,1731]" name="United States of America" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">US</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion box="[700,787,1704,1731]" country="United States of America" name="Florida" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Florida</collectingRegion>
); other countries in the Caribbean Sea, 
<collectingCountry box="[1221,1311,1705,1731]" name="Guyana" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Guyana</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[1368,1436,1704,1730]" name="Brazil" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="van Soest, R. W. M." box="[159,337,1741,1767]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="1 - 225" refId="ref81605" refString="van Soest, R. W. M. (2017) Sponges of the Guyana Shelf. Zootaxa, 4217 (1), 1 - 225. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4217.1.1" type="journal article" year="2017">van Soest 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="39" pageNumber="40" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,1164,1947]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1777,1803]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Remarks.</emphasis>
Only two species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Laubenfels" authorityYear="1949" box="[564,700,1777,1802]" class="Demospongiae" family="Petrosiidae" genus="Neopetrosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Porifera" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[564,700,1777,1802]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Neopetrosia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been reported in the northern GoM, 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Lamarck" baseAuthorityYear="1814" box="[1190,1351,1776,1802]" class="Demospongiae" family="Petrosiidae" genus="Neopetrosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="carbonaria">
<emphasis box="[1190,1351,1776,1802]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">N. carbonaria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Rutzler et al. 2009)" baseAuthorityName="Rutzler" baseAuthorityYear="2009" class="Demospongiae" family="Petrosiidae" genus="Neopetrosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="subtriangularis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">N. subtriangularis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Rutzler, K. &amp; Soest, R. W. M. Van &amp; Piantoni, C." box="[339,555,1812,1839]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="285 - 313" refId="ref80876" refString="Rutzler, K., Soest, R. W. M. Van &amp; Piantoni, C. (2009) Sponges (Porifera) of the Gulf of Mexico. In: Felder, D. L. &amp; Camp, D. K. (Eds.), Gulf of Mexico Origin, Waters, and Biota. Texas A &amp; M Press, College Station, Texas, pp. 285 - 313." type="book chapter" year="2009">
Rützler 
<emphasis box="[430,487,1812,1838]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[573,779,1812,1838]" class="Demospongiae" family="Petrosiidae" genus="Neopetrosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="subtriangularis">
<emphasis box="[573,779,1812,1838]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">N. subtriangularis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been also reported in the southern section of the GoM (
<emphasis box="[161,201,1849,1874]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">e.g.</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Green, G." box="[215,350,1849,1875]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="79 - 98" refId="ref76592" refString="Green, G. (1977) Sinopsis Taxonomica de esponjas de la Blanquilla. Anales del Centro de Ciencias del Mar y Limnologia, Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, 1, 79 - 98." type="journal article" year="1977">Green 1977</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Green, G. &amp; Fuentes, V. L. &amp; Gomez, P." box="[361,559,1848,1875]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="9 - 11" refId="ref76629" refString="Green, G., Fuentes, V. L. &amp; Gomez, P. (1986) Nuevos registros de Porifera del arrecife la Blanquilla, Veracruz Mexico. Anales del Centro de Ciencias del Mar y Limnologia, Universidad Nacional Autonoma de Mexico, 27, 9 - 11." type="journal article" year="1986">
Green 
<emphasis box="[437,493,1848,1874]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">et al.</emphasis>
1986
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Gomez, P." box="[571,720,1849,1875]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="51 - 72" refId="ref76106" refString="Gomez, P. (2007) Inventario de las esponjas del Parque Nacional Sistema Arrecifal Veracruzano, con nuevos Registros de Especies (Porifera: Demospongiae). In: Jimenez-Hernandez, M. J.; Granados-Barba, A. &amp; Ortiz-Lozano, L. (Eds.), Investigaciones Cientificas en el Sistema Arrecifal Veracruzano. Universidad Autonoma de Campeche, Campeche, pp. 51 - 72." type="book chapter" year="2007">Gómez 2007</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName box="[738,973,1849,1874]" class="Demospongiae" family="Petrosiidae" genus="Neopetrosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="proxima">
<emphasis box="[738,973,1849,1874]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Neopetrosia proxima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has also been reported in 
<collectingCountry box="[1266,1353,1849,1875]" name="Guyana" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Guyana</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="van Soest, R. W. M." pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="1 - 225" refId="ref81605" refString="van Soest, R. W. M. (2017) Sponges of the Guyana Shelf. Zootaxa, 4217 (1), 1 - 225. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4217.1.1" type="journal article" year="2017">van Soest (2017)</bibRefCitation>
. Our study is the first record of 
<taxonomicName box="[659,784,1885,1910]" class="Demospongiae" family="Petrosiidae" genus="Neopetrosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Haplosclerida" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="proxima">
<emphasis box="[659,784,1885,1910]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">N. proxima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the GoM, since it has not been recorded in any recent revision study of sponges from the region (
<bibRefCitation author="Gomez, P." box="[632,781,1921,1947]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="51 - 72" refId="ref76106" refString="Gomez, P. (2007) Inventario de las esponjas del Parque Nacional Sistema Arrecifal Veracruzano, con nuevos Registros de Especies (Porifera: Demospongiae). In: Jimenez-Hernandez, M. J.; Granados-Barba, A. &amp; Ortiz-Lozano, L. (Eds.), Investigaciones Cientificas en el Sistema Arrecifal Veracruzano. Universidad Autonoma de Campeche, Campeche, pp. 51 - 72." type="book chapter" year="2007">Gómez 2007</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Rutzler, K. &amp; Soest, R. W. M. Van &amp; Piantoni, C." box="[793,1004,1920,1947]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="285 - 313" refId="ref80876" refString="Rutzler, K., Soest, R. W. M. Van &amp; Piantoni, C. (2009) Sponges (Porifera) of the Gulf of Mexico. In: Felder, D. L. &amp; Camp, D. K. (Eds.), Gulf of Mexico Origin, Waters, and Biota. Texas A &amp; M Press, College Station, Texas, pp. 285 - 313." type="book chapter" year="2009">
Rützler 
<emphasis box="[882,938,1920,1946]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Ugalde, D. &amp; Gomez, P. &amp; Simoes, N." box="[1016,1228,1920,1947]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="151 - 183" refId="ref82484" refString="Ugalde, D., Gomez, P. &amp; Simoes, N. (2015) Marine sponges (Porifera: Demospongiae) from the Gulf of Mexico, new records and redescription of Erylus trisphaerus (de Laubenfels, 1953). Zootaxa, 3911 (2), 151 - 183. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3911.2.1" type="journal article" year="2015">
Ugalde 
<emphasis box="[1104,1160,1920,1946]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">et al.</emphasis>
2015
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
